#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/polynomial/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.polynomial:28
msgid ""
"These *convenience classes* provide a consistent interface for creating, "
"manipulating, and fitting data with polynomials of different bases. The "
"convenience classes are the preferred interface for the `~numpy.polynomial` "
"package, and are available from the ``numpy.polynomial`` namespace. This "
"eliminates the need to navigate to the corresponding submodules, e.g. ``np."
"polynomial.Polynomial`` or ``np.polynomial.Chebyshev`` instead of ``np."
"polynomial.polynomial.Polynomial`` or ``np.polynomial.chebyshev.Chebyshev``, "
"respectively. The classes provide a more consistent and concise interface "
"than the type-specific functions defined in the submodules for each type of "
"polynomial. For example, to fit a Chebyshev polynomial with degree ``1`` to "
"data given by arrays ``xdata`` and ``ydata``, the `~chebyshev.Chebyshev.fit` "
"class method::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/polynomial/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.polynomial:42
msgid ""
">>> from numpy.polynomial import Chebyshev\n"
">>> xdata = [1, 2, 3, 4]\n"
">>> ydata = [1, 4, 9, 16]\n"
">>> c = Chebyshev.fit(xdata, ydata, deg=1)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/polynomial/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.polynomial:47
msgid ""
"is preferred over the `chebyshev.chebfit` function from the ``np.polynomial."
"chebyshev`` module::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/polynomial/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.polynomial:50
msgid ""
">>> from numpy.polynomial.chebyshev import chebfit\n"
">>> c = chebfit(xdata, ydata, deg=1)"
msgstr ""

